<figureCitation box="[290,373,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1829,1853]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-18@25.[151,1436,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 13. Tonicia forbesii, SEM images of a specimen BL 15.2 mm; A, detail of ocelli system in lateral area of intermediate valve IV;B,radularteeth;C, detail of minorandmajor lateral teeth; D, detail ofintermediate valveIV.Acanthochitona arragonites, disarticulated valves of a specimen BL 8.7 mm, Las Salinas, Copala (CNMO 5267). Valves in dorsal view shows the sculpturing details; E, head valve; F, intermediate valve IV; G, tail valve. Valves in ventral view, H, head valve; I, intermediate valve IV; J, tail valve. SEM images of a specimen BL 9.1 mm; valves in dorsal view, K, head valve in dorsal view." pageId="21" pageNumber="472">13E–K</figureCitation>
